# S08-T03: Emotion Animations

## Objective
Give each emotion a distinct GSAP performance in `useMascotAnimation`, so reactions read
clearly to a 5–11 audience. Body motion + face extras animate together.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Per-state timelines: happy (hop+bounce), celebrate (spin/jump + sparkle pop),
  wink (one lid blink + cheek raise), wrong (shake + sweat drop), sad (wilt/scale-down + brow down),
  hurry (fast nervous bob + sweat), sleepy (slow sway + zzz fade-in), idle (breathe/float).
- Each non-idle emotion returns to `idle` on complete.
- Extras (`sweat`/`sparkle`/`zzz`) fade in/out within their emotion only.
- All tweens killed on unmount / state change (no leaks, no overlap).
- Easings match DESIGN.md Animation Palette where specified.

## Steps
1. Extend `useMascotAnimation` to accept the new `MascotState` union + extra refs.
2. Implement a `Record<MascotState, () => gsap.core.Timeline>` factory.
3. Drive extras opacity inside the relevant timelines.
4. Keep `useLevelUpFlash` / `useScreenShake` unchanged.
5. `git commit -m "feat(mascot): distinct GSAP performance per emotion"`.
